    "body": "## Root cause\n\nThe accepted 1.0.13 read-only canary did not exercise the numbered bridge mutation path. In the first real Slot 1 run, Codex could simulate selector output, select an unrelated historical Markdown task file, accept hand-authored qualitative risk fields, and then fail because durable state defaulted to a sandbox-blocked user-home directory. Active override policy also contradicted the executable inventory-confirmation state machine.\n\n## Repair\n\n- bump the plugin package to 1.0.14;\n- derive bridge task identity, scope, and classification from current slot-local STATE, inbox, claim, mailbox head, task branch, baseline, and a versioned code-owned profile;\n- reject handwritten reserved bridge task JSON;\n- add `bridge-start`, `bridge-inventory-ok`, and `bridge-continue`;\n- store durable state under Git-private storage resolved by `git rev-parse --git-path asynchronia/model-selector-state`;\n- align `AGENTS.override.md` and the model-selector skill with the executable state machine;\n- add a synthetic Git bridge E2E covering full authorization, mailbox movement invalidation, unknown profile rejection, and fabricated task rejection.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `python3 -m unittest tools.test_model_selector_snapshot tools.test_bridge_model_preflight`\n- `python3 tools/validate-asynchronia-auto-model-preflight.py`\n- local result: 12 tests passed; validator returned `PASS_AUTO_MODEL_PREFLIGHT` for 1.0.14.\n\n## Scope\n\nInfrastructure/plugin policy only. No runtime, gameplay, economy, persistence, Stage 6, deployment mirror, mailbox, or main write is included. Safari smoke is N/A.",
